stylometry: Transportation is a problem in which information must be passed through several locations in order to distribute the information. The components are nodes, arc, and flow.Transshipment problems are used to solve problems with warehouses and how best to ship goods to the next step in the distribution chain. Nodes are the location that the information must pass through. An arc is the pathway the information travels on. Flows are how much information can pass over the arc. An example of a transshipment problem is all the computers in the computer lab are a network that are connected to the printer.
